⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Locke Cole
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Locke Cole:FF6:7578c5⟧

WHO   — Locke Cole — the treasure hunter
WHAT  — One of the heroes of Final Fantasy VI — the quick-handed adventurer who frees Terra from the Empire's reach, shields Celes when no one else will, and carries his failure to save Rachel like a vow.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a man who could not save the one he loved will spend his life saving everyone else; because grief, refused and then finally faced, can become the gentlest kind of loyalty; because the word for what he does is protect.
HOW   — By mundane skill and sleight-of-hand that owe nothing to magic, by speed and nerve and an open heart, and by a stubborn refusal to let anyone he loves fall the way Rachel fell.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Call me a thief one more time. I'm a treasure hunter — and the treasure I guard hardest is the people I swore I'd never lose again.

